## 👑 PHASE 3: MASTER NODE ONLY

> ⚠️ **Machi:** Indha phase commands MASTER node la MATTUM run pannu!

### Step 10: Cluster Initialize Pannu

```bash
sudo kubeadm init \
  --pod-network-cidr=10.244.0.0/16 \
  --apiserver-advertise-address=<MASTER-PRIVATE-IP>

# Example:
# sudo kubeadm init \
#   --pod-network-cidr=10.244.0.0/16 \
#   --apiserver-advertise-address=172.31.10.5
```

```
✅ Output la ipdhi varum:
Your Kubernetes control-plane has initialized successfully!

To start using your cluster, you need to run the following as regular user:
  mkdir -p $HOME/.kube
  ...

Then you can join any number of worker nodes by running the following on each as root:
kubeadm join 172.31.10.5:6443 --token xxxxx \
    --discovery-token-ca-cert-hash sha256:xxxxx

⚠️ MACHI IMPORTANT: Indha join command COPY panniko! Worker ku venum!
```

### Step 11: Kubeconfig Setup (Master la)

```bash
mkdir -p $HOME/.kube
sudo cp -i /etc/kubernetes/admin.conf $HOME/.kube/config
sudo chown $(id -u):$(id -g) $HOME/.kube/config

# Verify
kubectl get nodes
# NAME         STATUS     ROLES           AGE
# k8s-master   NotReady   control-plane   1m
# (NotReady - network plugin install aagala, okay!)
```

### Step 12: Network Plugin Install (Flannel)

```bash
kubectl apply -f \
  https://raw.githubusercontent.com/flannel-io/flannel/master/Documentation/kube-flannel.yml

# Wait 30 seconds, then check
kubectl get nodes
# NAME         STATUS   ROLES           AGE
# k8s-master   Ready    control-plane   3m ✅

kubectl get pods -n kube-flannel
# ✅ All Running irukkanum
```

